description: 1006F..1958 Corvette Convertible Hardtop, radio delete, 283-290 hp, (fuelie), 4 speed, the "Chitwood Thrill Show Corvette" was ordered new by legendary Joie Chitwood of "Thrill Show" fame and was built in January 1958. This matching numbers historic Corvette has less than 19,000 original miles. After undergoing a professional nut and bolt restoration the story of the Chitwood Corvette was a featured cover story in Corvette Fever magazine. NCRS American Heritage award at Denver National Convention in July 2015. These type restorations normally cost between $80,000.00 to $125,000.00. Joie Chitwood started his racing career in Winfield, Kansas, twice winning the AAA East Coast Sprint car championship and winning the CSRA title in 1942. He competed at the Indianapolis 500 seven times, finishing fifth on three different occasions and he was the first man ever to wear a safety belt at the Indy 500. Most all factory correct type components including the spare, jack, jack tools, trunk mat, trunk liner, rebound straps, seat belts, T-10 transmission, 4:11 posi rear end, shifter, air cleaner, generator, hoses, hose clamps, valve covers, F.I. unit, F.I. fuel filter, guide Y-50 mirror, washboard hood, trunk irons, owners manual, sales brochure, and T-3 headlights. Substantial documentation is included with this vehicle, including original Joie Chitwood promotional materials, video footage of Chitwoods Thrill Show, owner history, the original 1958 registration signed by Joie Chitwood and all registrations thereafter. Click here to read more about Joie Chitwood and this Corvette and/or Click here to watch the 10-minute GM promotional film Joie Chitwood's "Thrill Driver's Choice". This is a beautiful, historic, and highly documented vehicle that has been professionally maintained and displayed in climate controlled conditions.

title: 1959 Chevrolet Corvette

description: Gateway Classic Cars of St. Louis is proud to offer a beautiful 1959 Chevrolet Corvette Fuelie.  Introduced in 1957, mechanical fuel injection was offered on Corvettes as a higher horsepower variant of the standard cars.  In 1959 this meant your choice of a 250 Horsepower or 290 Horsepower 283 CID V8 with no carburetor to be found.  745 buyers chose the $484.20 option to get the 290 HP Fuelie.  This particular example is beautifully optioned in Snowcrest White with silver coves and black interior.  She wears the appropriate hub caps with knock offs wrapped in wide white wall tires.  The chrome trim on this particular car is in great shape and makes for a dazzling piece of eye candy.  Inside you'll find more chrome and stainless trim to accent the black upholstery.  You'll also find another very rare option: power windows, which only 587 buyers chose in 1959.  Driving enthusiasts will be delighted to see that behind the 290 HP v8 is a proper 4 speed manual transmission.  Speaking of the drive train, the engine has been completely rebuild, and perhaps even more importantly, the fuel injection system has been rebuilt by an expert that specializes in these systems.  The car runs beautifully and is a delight to pilot down the road.  Being a Fuelie, and therefore quite rare, this is a true collector's piece.  This car would be at home in the most avid Corvette collector's garage.  You can see this awesome 1959 Chevrolet Corvette Fuelie in greater detail in our St. Louis showroom or at www.GatewayClassicCars.com.  Please contact 618-271-2000 or STL@gatewayclassiccars.com with inquires.
